Package com.example.breadheadsinventorymanager

Class User

java.lang.Object
com.example.breadheadsinventorymanager.User
All Implemented Interfaces:
FirestorePuttable
public class User extends Object implements FirestorePuttable
Represents a User that can be put onto Firestore. Uses the user's ID retrieved from the GoogleSignInAccount system. Technically insecure; authentication isn't handled here, but rather in the Firestore database permission settings (so the exact specifics of the validation system depend on the needs of the user). For the project submission, no security measures are in place to ensure testing TAs don't encounter any roadblocks when trying to access the database.
